This is TbxAppGen generated application.

It shows an icon on the the iconbar with program information and quit options.
Dropping a file on the icon bar icon shows a window that can be modified to display the file contents.

It includes:
  !Boot a simple boot file
  !Run a simple run file that defines the application directory
  !Sprites the application sprite
  Messages a minimal messages file
  Res the toolbox resources file
  cc.main the c++ source for the main entry point
  h.IconbarHandler - setup iconbar so a filename dropped on it will open a window for the filename
  h.%APPNAME%Wnd, cc.%APPNAME%Wnd - declaration and implemention of the  %APPNAME%Wnd class which can be used to setup attach and process event handlers for the Window resource and load the file.

  Makefile a makefile to build the project

Things that need to be done
  Design you own sprite
  Update the Program Information dialogue
  Modify the Window resource to be suitable for your application.
  Add code to the %APPNAME%Wnd class to do your processing including loading of the file.
  Replace the !Help file with your own content.
  Set the Wimpslot in the !Run file to a sensible value
